cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with understanding human social behaviors in raw image sequences, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a neural network architecture that is trained end-to-end, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a Recurrent Neural Network for temporal consistency suggests the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with detecting multiple individuals, which is a problem in robotics, suggesting the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with recognizing collective activities, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
